reviews.text: Just a one way system, very busy with with cars because there are too many traffic lights 🚥

The "Poor 2*" rating is for the state of the toilets ( men's AND Disabled )...The men's toilets are always seemingly  out of use whenever I pass through on the way to Sheerness on Sea and  the disabled toilets yesterday were full to overflowing and unable to flush...The good news is the information services on the platform and High Speed service to St Pancras is 1st class...Seating on the platform is adequate and generally clean,but the toilets are a disgrace

Rather average station with fast services to Dover, Ramsgate and London as well as services towards Sheerness. The station has a car park, taxi rank and a ticket office near some ticket barriers and is decent in appearance if you ask me. Lifts are also provided here but don't expect the services here to be adequate in the rush hours.
